ADDITIONAL REQUIREMENTS FOR DERIVATIVE WORKS AND MODIFICATIONS:

Any person or entity creating derivative works, modifications, forks, or 
redistributions of this Software MUST comply with the following mandatory 
requirements:

1. PLAYER2 INTEGRATION PRESERVATION:
   - Player2 must remain available as an AI provider option
   - The original Player2 implementation must be maintained and functional
   - Player2 cannot be removed, disabled, or made non-functional

2. GAME CLIENT ID REQUIREMENT:
   - Must use the exact Game Client ID: "019a8368-b00b-72bc-b367-2825079dc6fb"
   - This ID cannot be changed, modified, or substituted
   - This ID must be used for all Player2 API communications

3. HEALTH CHECK IMPLEMENTATION:
   - Must implement automated health check calls to Player2 API
   - Health checks must occur every 60 seconds when Player2 is active
   - Health check functionality cannot be disabled or removed

4. AUTHENTICATION PRESERVATION:
   - Original Player2 authentication methods must be preserved
   - Authentication flow must remain compatible with Player2 specifications
   - Cannot modify or break Player2's authentication mechanism

5. ATTRIBUTION REQUIREMENT:
   - Must include prominent credit to the original author (CarlosNahuelcoy)
   - Attribution must be visible in user-facing documentation and interfaces
   - Cannot claim original authorship of Player2 integration components

6. API COMPLIANCE:
   - Must maintain compliance with Player2 API requirements
   - Cannot modify API calls in ways that break Player2 functionality
   - Must preserve all Player2-specific headers and request formats

ENFORCEMENT:
Failure to comply with ANY of these additional requirements constitutes a 
material breach of this license and terminates all rights granted herein.
Legal action may be taken to enforce compliance with these terms.

PERMITTED ACTIVITIES:
- Adding new AI providers alongside Player2
- Improving existing functionality while preserving Player2
- Bug fixes that don't remove Player2 requirements
- UI/UX improvements that maintain Player2 access
- Performance optimizations that preserve Player2 functionality

